66
00:05:06,892 --> 00:05:08,532
All right.

67
00:05:08,532 --> 00:05:11,632
Since you joined us, this furniture boutique

68
00:05:11,632 --> 00:05:15,603
has become one of the best-performing shops.

69
00:05:15,603 --> 00:05:18,542
Have you set the sales goal for next year?

70
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:21,843
What's the goal?

71
00:05:21,843 --> 00:05:26,212
Various indexes that directly affect furniture sales, such as the country's birthrate and marriage rate,

72
00:05:26,212 --> 00:05:29,283
keep on dropping drastically every year.

73
00:05:29,283 --> 00:05:32,422
We should be as conservative as possible when setting the goal...

74
00:05:32,422 --> 00:05:37,562
Do Jun, you should get this CEO of yours a pair of reading glasses.

75
00:05:37,562 --> 00:05:42,833
I guess his eyesight is bad. He can see one thing but not the other.

76
00:05:42,833 --> 00:05:44,002
Pardon me?

77
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:51,733
Even if the population decreases, the number of single-person households will continue to rise.

78
00:05:51,733 --> 00:05:55,642
In that case, instead of barely selling a couch to each household,

79
00:05:55,642 --> 00:06:00,442
we'll be able to sell a couch for each room.

80
00:06:02,010 --> 00:06:05,083
What's your problem? Do you not want to earn money?

81
00:06:05,083 --> 00:06:07,652
I was shortsighted, Chairman.

82
00:06:07,652 --> 00:06:09,552
Please forgive me.

83
00:06:14,963 --> 00:06:19,832
Get your calculations right. Once you have set the sales goal, submit it to me.

84
00:06:19,832 --> 00:06:21,002
Yes, Sir.

85
00:06:21,002 --> 00:06:24,232
How would you face your wife if you got fired before your contract ended?

86
00:06:31,982 --> 00:06:35,113
As for CEO Jin... It's not only circumstantial.

87
00:06:35,113 --> 00:06:37,023
We have firm evidence that she committed embezzlement.

88
00:06:37,023 --> 00:06:39,653
Yet you want me to wrap it up as a case of non-indictment?

89
00:06:39,653 --> 00:06:42,952
What's the problem? She paid back what she had embezzled.

90
00:06:42,952 --> 00:06:44,793
- Sir. 
 - Prosecutor Seo.

91
00:06:44,793 --> 00:06:48,233
You're young. Keep up with the trends, will you?

92
00:06:48,233 --> 00:06:51,262
The ability to think flexibly is important in the 21st century.

93
00:06:51,262 --> 00:06:55,873
I always thought it was such a shame that we were settling for a punishment-focused justice system.

94
00:06:55,873 --> 00:07:00,842
It's about time the prosecution contributed to paving the way for reconciliation and forgiveness.

95
00:07:00,842 --> 00:07:04,742
While she lost 140 billion won  ($140M)  due to a speculative investment,

96
00:07:04,742 --> 00:07:08,382
a total of 37 businesses went bankrupt,

97
00:07:08,382 --> 00:07:12,223
and 946 people lost their jobs.

98
00:07:12,223 --> 00:07:17,092
Has she compensated the victims for their suffering?

99
00:07:17,890 --> 00:07:19,962
Reconciliation and forgiveness?

100
00:07:19,962 --> 00:07:23,692
Forcing the victims to forgive.

101
00:07:23,692 --> 00:07:26,562
Do you call that restorative justice?

102
00:07:26,562 --> 00:07:29,433
Aren't you doing this because you wish to reconcile with Soonyang?

103
00:07:29,433 --> 00:07:33,073
Look, Prosecutor Seo Min Yeong.

104
00:07:34,470 --> 00:07:37,312
Prosecutors have the right to prosecute crimes.

105
00:07:37,312 --> 00:07:40,453
I'd like to exercise my rights and indict CEO Jin.

106
00:07:40,453 --> 00:07:43,852
Please help me, Sir.

107
00:07:52,420 --> 00:07:55,463
This is why I don't like working with women.

108
00:07:55,463 --> 00:07:57,732
Hey, I bet you don't know

109
00:07:57,732 --> 00:08:01,333
why female prosecutors never get the key positions.

110
00:08:01,333 --> 00:08:03,932
You never served in the army so you don't know how to work
in an organization.

111
00:08:03,932 --> 00:08:05,943
Article Seven of the Prosecutors' Office Act.

112
00:08:05,943 --> 00:08:08,713
The Principle of Identity of Public Prosecutors. Don't you know?

113
00:08:08,713 --> 00:08:13,112
"Obey any order of your superiors." Just do as I say, you little brat!

114
00:08:18,252 --> 00:08:20,153
I should get going.

115
00:08:21,520 --> 00:08:23,823
- Grandfather. 
 - Yes, I'm fine. I'm fine.

116
00:08:23,823 --> 00:08:26,563
- Are you all right? 
 - I'm totally fine. I'm okay.

117
00:08:40,270 --> 00:08:43,642
- Here, have some water, Grandfather. 
 - What? Okay, thanks.

118
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:03,592
Hey, take a seat.

119
00:09:03,592 --> 00:09:04,932
Okay.

120
00:09:09,902 --> 00:09:12,803
Keep this to yourself, Do Jun.

121
00:09:16,213 --> 00:09:19,682
The doctors at Soonyang medical center wanted to run some tests on me,

122
00:09:19,682 --> 00:09:23,013
so I took some X-rays.

123
00:09:23,823 --> 00:09:27,553
What did the results say? Are you undergoing treatment?

124
00:09:29,723 --> 00:09:32,363
For others, only their organs show up on their X-rays.

125
00:09:32,363 --> 00:09:38,533
But below my chest, I have three things that others don't have.

126
00:09:39,433 --> 00:09:41,032
Here resides my greed for money.

127
00:09:41,032 --> 00:09:44,403
Here lies my distrust of those who work for me.

128
00:09:44,403 --> 00:09:46,872
And down here...

129
00:09:46,872 --> 00:09:49,242
is where you'd find

130
00:09:49,242 --> 00:09:52,043
my ability

131
00:09:52,043 --> 00:09:54,583
to betray anyone,

132
00:09:56,850 --> 00:09:58,653
anytime.

133
00:10:09,430 --> 00:10:11,133
You see,

134
00:10:11,860 --> 00:10:16,173
I grew Soonyang into what it is today with those three things.

135
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:20,542
Did you say you wanted to buy Soonyang?

136
00:10:22,740 --> 00:10:25,183
You won't be able to,

137
00:10:25,910 --> 00:10:29,483
if all you've got is what everyone else has.

138
00:10:40,830 --> 00:10:46,432
Let them do the work.

139
00:10:47,270 --> 00:10:53,332
But never trust them.

140
00:10:54,210 --> 00:10:57,542
Hwa Young ended up in that mess because she trusted her employees.

141
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:08,052
Do not trust anyone.

142
00:11:08,850 --> 00:11:12,063
Do not open up to anyone.

143
00:11:13,260 --> 00:11:17,533
If you do, it'll end up

144
00:11:18,530 --> 00:11:20,832
becoming nothing but your weakness.

145
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:28,542
You little rascal.

146
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:32,583
I'm off.

147
00:11:40,420 --> 00:11:46,963
Then I may distrust you and betray you too, Grandfather.

148
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:52,633
Will that be okay?

149
00:11:58,640 --> 00:12:00,542
Do Jun.

150
00:12:02,140 --> 00:12:08,283
Do you think I trust you?

151
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:20,992
Oh, Dear.

152
00:12:42,812 --> 00:12:45,682
The case has been reassigned to a different prosecutor.

153
00:12:45,682 --> 00:12:47,192
It's obvious.

154
00:12:47,192 --> 00:12:48,723
You're a woman of principle.

155
00:12:48,723 --> 00:12:51,792
You'd never blindly obey Chief,

156
00:12:51,792 --> 00:12:54,293
so I bet this was the only way.

157
00:12:59,302 --> 00:13:01,672
I know you worked hard on the case.

158
00:13:01,672 --> 00:13:04,602
I'm sorry this happened.

159
00:13:04,602 --> 00:13:08,442
This means I won't have to work late for a while. This is great.

160
00:13:09,642 --> 00:13:12,642
Well, since we have nothing to do today,

161
00:13:12,642 --> 00:13:15,253
why don't we leave right on the dot for once?

162
00:13:15,253 --> 00:13:16,782
Like other civil servants.

163
00:13:16,782 --> 00:13:19,122
Bye, I'm off.

164
00:13:32,733 --> 00:13:34,472
Let's meet up.

165
00:13:47,713 --> 00:13:51,422
You knew from the beginning.

166
00:13:52,353 --> 00:13:55,393
That I wouldn't be able to indict CEO Jin,

167
00:13:55,393 --> 00:13:58,223
