Fellow Korean Lad,

774
00:57:46,953 --> 00:57:50,523
you did change the flow.

775
00:57:54,993 --> 00:57:58,093
   

776
00:57:58,993 --> 00:58:02,363
Isn't this all wrong?

777
00:58:02,363 --> 00:58:03,502
   

778
00:58:03,502 --> 00:58:08,773
How can the KOSPI index be on the rise already?

779
00:58:09,513 --> 00:58:11,373
Answer me!

780
00:58:13,213 --> 00:58:16,342
Over 3,000 died in a terrorist attack in the center of New York.

781
00:58:16,342 --> 00:58:19,853
So how, why, how on earth...

782
00:58:19,853 --> 00:58:23,593
How could things recover after just one month?

783
00:58:23,593 --> 00:58:26,592
Where are all the people who said there'd be a war?

784
00:58:26,592 --> 00:58:29,193
Why is everything so peaceful?

785
00:58:29,193 --> 00:58:32,233
   

786
00:58:32,233 --> 00:58:35,962
The US lowered the interest rate, improving liquidity.

787
00:58:37,002 --> 00:58:40,072
Future stocks sold at a record high,

788
00:58:40,072 --> 00:58:42,543
so the ten billion won  ($10M)  you invested in put options,

789
00:58:42,543 --> 00:58:46,712
in case the market crashed, was lost.

790
00:58:48,382 --> 00:58:52,212
No one could have foreseen this kind of bull market.

791
00:58:52,212 --> 00:58:54,083
Miracle Investment's Buy Miracle fund.

792
00:58:54,083 --> 00:58:59,953
Who could've thought they'd create such a dramatic turnaround in the Korean market?

793
00:58:59,953 --> 00:59:02,492
Why you...

794
00:59:06,032 --> 00:59:09,332
Sir, you have a visitor.

795
00:59:20,313 --> 00:59:22,382
Hello, Mr. Baek.

796
00:59:23,113 --> 00:59:24,883
Thank you.

797
00:59:30,152 --> 00:59:32,423
Hello, Uncle.

798
00:59:37,263 --> 00:59:39,333
"Buy Miracle?"

799
00:59:39,333 --> 00:59:42,632
You scraped together what little you had to launch a successful fund,

800
00:59:42,632 --> 00:59:47,332
and you're acting like a victorious hero.

801
00:59:47,332 --> 00:59:50,713
Do you think I don't know? You also...

802
00:59:50,713 --> 00:59:53,183
You lost just as much as I did.

803
00:59:53,183 --> 00:59:55,082
The airlines, travel agencies, hotels, and insurance companies

804
00:59:55,082 --> 00:59:58,112
you'd invested in through the New York Stock Exchange.

805
00:59:58,112 --> 01:00:03,353
Do you think I don't know you lost all that in the 9-11 terrorist attacks?

806
01:00:03,353 --> 01:00:05,422
Oh, that?

807
01:00:06,222 --> 01:00:12,392
New York Air, the Lavender Hotel chain, Seventy Insurance, and Tour Eagles?

808
01:00:13,433 --> 01:00:15,402
How odd.

809
01:00:15,402 --> 01:00:18,602
Miracle's investment portfolio is top secret.

810
01:00:18,602 --> 01:00:22,942
How do you know all that?

811
01:00:28,842 --> 01:00:33,382
You can't let in a neighbor's dog just because they're cute.

812
01:00:35,683 --> 01:00:38,323
It will be your loss if it bites you.

813
01:00:40,993 --> 01:00:43,423
You punk!

814
01:00:54,402 --> 01:00:56,973
Why did you come here?

815
01:00:58,473 --> 01:01:01,442
Did you come here to lecture me?

816
01:01:01,442 --> 01:01:03,413
No.

817
01:01:04,152 --> 01:01:09,353
I'm here to buy Soonyang Investment.

818
01:01:10,353 --> 01:01:12,022
What?

819
01:01:24,132 --> 01:01:26,373
Regardless of the country's economy,

820
01:01:26,373 --> 01:01:28,902
regardless of whether your customers lose their savings,

821
01:01:28,902 --> 01:01:33,472
you're praying the market will crash when you're the head of an investment company.

822
01:01:33,472 --> 01:01:36,513
I can't let you stay in charge any longer.

823
01:01:40,382 --> 01:01:42,253
Do Jun.

824
01:01:44,723 --> 01:01:46,593
Do Jun!

825
01:01:50,132 --> 01:01:55,163
Do you think the world will go the way you want?

826
01:01:59,773 --> 01:02:01,642
Of course not.

827
01:02:02,473 --> 01:02:04,412
Oh, right.

828
01:02:05,143 --> 01:02:07,842
The National Pension, Teachers' Pension,

829
01:02:07,842 --> 01:02:14,153
and Pension and Funds Bureau decided to cut ties with Soonyang Investment.

830
01:02:15,582 --> 01:02:17,352
What?

831
01:02:17,352 --> 01:02:21,810
Oh, you didn't know?

832
01:02:30,373 --> 01:02:34,973
You lost over ten billion won  ($10M)  in a speculative put option investment,

833
01:02:34,973 --> 01:02:41,342
and they want to hold you responsible for the extreme and dogmatic decision.

834
01:02:41,982 --> 01:02:45,653
Uncle. The Pension and Funds Bureau.

835
01:02:45,653 --> 01:02:52,023
They're your largest client and second majority shareholder with a 12-percent stake.

836
01:02:52,023 --> 01:02:53,663
If they cut ties with you,

837
01:02:53,663 --> 01:02:58,963
does that mean selling their stake or canceling all transactions?

838
01:03:00,433 --> 01:03:04,803
No, wait. It could be both.

839
01:03:05,573 --> 01:03:07,572
Too bad.

840
01:03:14,842 --> 01:03:19,953
If Miracle were to take over and we appoint...

841
01:03:22,252 --> 01:03:23,223
   

842
01:03:23,223 --> 01:03:28,793
an investment expert, the worst can be avoided.

843
01:03:32,032 --> 01:03:36,402
A nephew takes the responsibility for his uncle's shortcomings.

844
01:03:40,143 --> 01:03:42,273
I like that picture.

845
01:03:51,783 --> 01:03:53,512
Here you go.

846
01:03:55,223 --> 01:03:59,160
- Have some coffee. 
 - Thank you.

847
01:04:04,663 --> 01:04:09,062
Mr. Ha. I have a question.

848
01:04:10,833 --> 01:04:15,002
You could've returned to work for Vice-Chairman Jin Dong Ki.

849
01:04:15,643 --> 01:04:18,272
Why did you choose me?

850
01:04:18,272 --> 01:04:22,612
I didn't make a choice.

851
01:04:23,252 --> 01:04:25,952
If I were to lose this job,

852
01:04:25,952 --> 01:04:30,323
it would only mean I'd messed up.

853
01:04:30,323 --> 01:04:35,022
Do you think anyone at Soonyang would take me back then?

854
01:04:37,893 --> 01:04:45,000
From the start, I was never allowed a choice.

855
01:04:45,933 --> 01:04:52,673
You were born into this family as 4-2, so you wouldn't get it.

856
01:04:52,673 --> 01:04:54,813
I'm 4-2?

857
01:04:57,652 --> 01:05:01,123
My gosh. I apologize.

858
01:05:03,453 --> 01:05:07,193
Chairman Jin's fourth son's second son.

859
01:05:07,193 --> 01:05:09,493
Is that it?

860
01:05:09,493 --> 01:05:11,032
Yes.

861
01:05:15,333 --> 01:05:20,732
That 4-2 asks you to do your best.

862
01:05:22,843 --> 01:05:24,343
Right.

863
01:05:25,942 --> 01:05:27,782
Thank you.

864
01:05:30,052 --> 01:05:31,983
Move.

865
01:05:33,652 --> 01:05:36,083
Where is Father?

866
01:05:36,083 --> 01:05:38,292
What a lovely sight.

867
01:05:38,292 --> 01:05:41,662
Mom. Where is Father?

868
01:05:41,662 --> 01:05:43,122
Father!

869
01:05:43,122 --> 01:05:44,232
Dong Ki!

870
01:05:44,232 --> 01:05:47,633
You, stay out of it.

871
01:05:47,633 --> 01:05:50,672
Father, where are you? Come on out!

872
01:05:50,672 --> 01:05:54,203
I have something to settle with the old man!

873
01:05:54,203 --> 01:05:56,673
Father, I have something to say!

874
01:05:56,673 --> 01:05:58,913
What's all this noise about?

875
01:06:04,483 --> 01:06:06,212
Father.

876
01:06:06,212 --> 01:06:08,822
I know everything.

877
01:06:10,752 --> 01:06:13,693
I know that you're behind Do Jun.

878
01:06:13,693 --> 01:06:16,893
I know that now.

879
01:06:16,893 --> 01:06:21,832
Hwa Young and I, the fact that we lost everything

880
01:06:21,832 --> 01:06:24,232
to our nephew, who's just a kid.

881
01:06:24,232 --> 01:06:28,702
It makes no sense unless you're behind him!

882
01:06:28,702 --> 01:06:31,573
- That's enough! 
 - Soonyang!

883
01:06:32,772 --> 01:06:36,613
You wanted Do Jun to take over from the very beginning.

884
01:06:36,613 --> 01:06:39,883
Isn't that so? Right?

885
01:06:39,883 --> 01:06:42,152
Why... Why is it...

886
01:06:42,152 --> 01:06:44,652
Why is it always me...

887
01:06:44,652 --> 01:06:49,823
Why am I always pushed to the wayside? Why?

888
01:06:54,002 --> 01:06:58,802
How much longer must I struggle and grovel?

889
01:06:58,802 --> 01:07:02,502
What can I do, what am I to do to make you care about me?

890
01:07:02,502 --> 01:07:04,613
For how long...

891
01:07:05,943 --> 01:07:08,743
How much longer must I live like this for?

892
01:07:08,743 --> 01:07:12,982
My gosh... Father.

893
01:07:18,223 --> 01:07:20,592
Father...

894
01:07:20,592 --> 01:07:23,962
Is that all he's capable of?

895
01:07:28,132 --> 01:07:30,333
I had no idea.

896
01:07:34,002 --> 01:07:36,173
Father.

897
01:07:36,173 --> 01:07:38,473
Father.

898
01:07:47,052 --> 01:07:49,283
It's cold out.

899
01:07:49,283 --> 01:07:51,992
I'm burning with fury inside.

900
01:07:54,393 --> 01:07:58,433
You must sort things out for them before it's too late.

901
01:07:59,332 --> 01:08:01,702
Making sure the siblings stay close is another way to protect Soonyang.

902
01:08:01,702 --> 01:08:06,232
It's only natural that they resent Do Jun.

903
01:08:06,232 --> 01:08:10,603
Hang Jae, do you also think Do Jun is going too far?

904
01:08:21,453 --> 01:08:23,183
What are you doing here?

905
01:08:23,183 --> 01:08:25,892
The chairman wants to see you.

906
01:08:30,493 --> 01:08:34,432
What? You look like you saw a ghost.

907
01:08:34,432 --> 01:08:36,802
You didn't call ahead.

908
01:08:36,802 --> 01:08:38,903
Get in.

909
01:08:38,903 --> 01:08:42,572
There's somewhere we must go.

910
01:09:01,793 --> 01:09:05,263
Do you think this is allowed?

911
01:09:06,093 --> 01:09:11,363
Hwa Young and Dong Ki are your aunt and uncle.

912
01:09:11,972 --> 01:09:14,072
They're my kids.

913
01:09:14,802 --> 01:09:17,102
Your father's siblings.

914
01:09:19,272 --> 01:09:22,243
Must you go to the very end?

915
01:09:24,513 --> 01:09:26,483
If need be.

916
01:09:27,152 --> 01:09:29,152
What?

917
01:09:29,152 --> 01:09:32,022
I guess I'm like you.

918
01:09:32,022 --> 01:09:35,962
I have three extra things in here.

919
01:09:35,962 --> 01:09:40,393
They're full of greed, suspicion, and change of mind.

920
01:09:40,393 --> 01:09:42,403
That's three.

921
01:10:04,152 --> 01:10:05,592
What?

922
01:10:07,363 --> 01:10:09,263
Are you sure?

923
01:10:11,162 --> 01:10:16,193
Father is with that rascal Do Jun?

924
01:10:16,193 --> 01:10:18,603
- What? 
 - A press conference is scheduled.

925
01:10:18,603 --> 01:10:23,342
Reporters from TV stations and the major papers are waiting for the chairman to arrive.

926
01:10:25,772 --> 01:10:28,483
He's going to make it official.

927
01:10:29,413 --> 01:10:32,283
Without even a word to us.

928
01:10:32,283 --> 01:10:33,682
   

929
01:10:33,682 --> 01:10:35,623
- Where's the chairman? 
 - What's going on?

930
01:10:35,623 --> 01:10:38,723
- Can you tell us what it's about? 
 - What do you know?

931
01:10:38,723 --> 01:10:39,592
Any comments, Sir?

932
01:10:39,592 --> 01:10:42,063
Calm down, please, everyone.

933
01:10:42,063 --> 01:10:46,333
This press conference is about Soonyang Financial Holding Company's establishment.

934
01:10:46,333 --> 01:10:49,162
We'll begin as soon as the chairman arrives, which will be shortly.

935
01:10:49,162 --> 01:10:50,903
Please bear with us.

936
01:10:50,903 --> 01:10:53,103
Is it true the holding company is to decide who his heir will be?

937
01:10:53,103 --> 01:10:54,272
Has he decided on someone?

938
01:10:54,272 --> 01:10:56,372
Will the new CEO become his successor?

939
01:10:56,372 --> 01:10:59,242
- Please tell us. 
 - Come on, now.

940
01:10:59,242 --> 01:11:03,513
Please ask those questions to the chairman himself.

941
01:11:04,252 --> 01:11:07,612
Do Jun, how about you run it?

942
01:11:09,053 --> 01:11:10,582
Pardon?

943
01:11:12,623 --> 01:11:15,193
Soonyang Financial Group.

944
01:11:16,962 --> 01:11:19,792
I'm going to give it to you.

945
01:11:47,863 --> 01:11:51,563
 Now I know the reason why 

946
01:11:52,863 --> 01:11:55,903
 I remember nothing about 4-2, Jin Do Jun. 

947
01:11:55,903 --> 01:11:58,772
   

948
01:11:58,772 --> 01:12:00,173
   

949
01:12:00,173 --> 01:12:02,872
 It's because I died. 

950
01:12:05,842 --> 01:12:07,582
 And... 

951
01:12:12,253 --> 01:12:17,582
 things that are bound to happen always happen, without fail. 

952
